  "text": "The list of possible nanoparticle effects is still lacunar, since there are very few relevant studies on the subject. The list should clearly be completed with the indirect effects, unrelated to nanoparticle accumulation in the brain. When exposure to nanoparticles is not sufficient to induce severe changes in the affected target organs or systems (liver, lungs, cardiovascular system, and circulating monocytes), it may however induce peripheral changes and result in indirect neurotoxicity, mediated by circulating cytokines synthesized by the affected organs. Cytokines are known to be able to promote the onset or the acceleration of brain disorders [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , whether they alter the integrity of the BBB or not [CITATION_3] .",
